To be more clear, you may need a new test case to verify real non-English characters. For example, your old method _dict_decode_to_str will run into an exception as below:

UnicodeEncodeError: 'ascii' codec can't encode character u'\xf1' in position 2: ordinal not in range(128)

You can try with below code piece:
a = {u'ni\xf1o': u'b', u'c': {u'a': u'd'}}
glance_replicator._dict_decode_to_str(a)
